&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secondment Opportunity ( 4- 6 months)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UHNM Employees Only - Applications from outside the Trust will not be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Ward Manager - RSUH Winter Escalation Ward &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated nurse with excellent clinical and leadership skills to join us on our winter escalation ward at RSUH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a fixed term contract of 4 months with the potential for it to be extended to 6 months over the winter period and would be of interest to Band 6 nurses looking to expand their managerial and leadership skills.&lt;br /&gt;The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in leading a team through change while ensuring both quality and safety are maintained to the highest standards. You should also have an innovative approach to delivering excellent care in line with budgetary expectations .&lt;br /&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;br /&gt;RGN Qualification&lt;br /&gt;Evidence of Degree Level Study&lt;br /&gt;Leadership Qualification&lt;br /&gt;Previous experience at Band 6 in Medicine &lt;br /&gt;Full Time Role 37.5 hours per week Monday - Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAmanda PatemanJob titleMatronEmail addressAmanda.Pateman@uhnm.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact via email&lt;/p&gt;
